snippet: Protest organizers said Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan had agreed to hold off on the development of an Istanbul park, pending a court ruling and a possible referendum.
abstract: Turkish protest organizers, whose fight to save Istanbul park set off political crisis, come to tentative agreement with Prime Min Recep Tayyip Erdogan that could end civil unrest;  say government has agreed to hold off on development of Gezi Park pending a court ruling and a possible referendum.

byline.contributor: Sebnem Arsu and Ceylan Yeginsu contributed reporting.

lead_paragraph: Protest organizers said Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan had agreed to hold off on the development of an Istanbul park, pending a court ruling and a possible referendum.

headline.main: Turkish Protesters Say Talks Lead to a Tentative Agreement
headline.print_headline: Turkish Protesters Say Talks With Premier Lead to a Tentative Agreement
